The DirectionalSound (20) (_dir) type is used to apply a small amount of spread and translation to a sound.

Fields:

Field name       Type      FileRef Default value      Description
ChildSound       metahash  dat54                      Child sound to be affected by directional changes
InnerAngle       float             30                 Unknown
OuterAngle       float             90                 Unknown
RearAttenuation  float             12                 Unknown
YawAngle         float             90                 Unknown
PitchAngle       float             0                  Unknown

Example:

<Item type="DirectionalSound">
 <Name>sirens_slow_dir3</Name>
 <Header>
  <Flags value="0x00008000" />
  <Category>vehicles_sirens</Category>
 </Header>
 <ChildSound>sirens_slow_dir3_sirens_slow</ChildSound>
 <InnerAngle value="20" />
 <OuterAngle value="65" />
 <RearAttenuation value="-3" />
 <YawAngle value="90" />
 <PitchAngle value="0" />
</Item>